<span class='line-number'>82</span>
<span class='line-number'>83</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;!/usr/bin/env bash&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Username&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;UBERNAME<span class="o">=</span><span class="k">$(</span>id -u -n<span class="k">)</span>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Create directory and database.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;mkdir ~/html/horde
</span><span class='line'>mysql -e <span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>CREATE DATABASE <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERNAME</span><span class="k">}</span>_horde<span class="p">;&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Remind the mysql password:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;cat ~/.my.cnf&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Copy php.ini, <span class="k">if</span> not existing.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;test -f ~/etc/php.ini <span class="o">||</span> cp -a /package/host/localhost/php-<span class="nv">$PHPVERSION</span>/lib/php.ini ~/etc/&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Config php.ini.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;perl -pi -e <span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>s<span class="p">|</span>^<span class="p">;</span>?include_path.*<span class="p">|</span><span class="nv">include_path</span><span class="o">=</span>.:<span class="nv">$HOME</span>/pear/php:/package/host/localhost/php-<span class="nv">$PHPVERSION</span>/lib/php<span class="p">|&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span> ~/etc/php.ini&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;<span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>Restart<span class="p">&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span> php.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;killall -u <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERNAME</span><span class="k">}</span> php-cgi&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Configure PEAR.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;pear config-create ~ ~/.pearrc
</span><span class='line'>pear channel-update pear.php.net
</span><span class='line'><span class="nb">cd</span> ~/pear
</span><span class='line'>pear install pear&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Install Horde.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;./pear channel-discover pear.horde.org
</span><span class='line'>./pear install horde/horde_role
</span><span class='line'>./pear run-scripts horde/horde_role&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Here you need to enter the installation directory.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;/home/&lt;UBERNAME&gt;/html/horde&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;For using your own domain make a symlink ln -s /home/<span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERNAME</span><span class="k">}</span>/html/horde /var/www/virtual/<span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERNAME</span><span class="k">}</span>/horde.domain.tld&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;./pear install -a -B horde/webmail&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Now it<span class="p">&amp;</span>rsquo<span class="p">;</span>s <span class="nb">time </span><span class="k">for</span> a little coffee.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;./webmail-install&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Here you need to give some informations.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;What database backend should we use?: mysql&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Username to connect to the database as* <span class="o">[]</span>: &lt;UBERNAME&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Password to connect with: Remember the mysql password&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;How should we connect to the database?: unix&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Location of UNIX socket <span class="o">[]</span>: &lt;ENTER&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Database name to use* <span class="o">[]</span>: &lt;UBERNAME&gt;_horde&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Internally used charset* <span class="o">[</span>utf-8<span class="o">]</span>: utf-8&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Use SSL to connect to the server?: <span class="o">(</span>1<span class="o">)</span> Yes&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Certification Authority to use <span class="k">for</span> SSL connections <span class="o">[]</span>: &lt;ENTER&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Split reads to a different server?: <span class="nb">false</span>&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Specify an existing mail user who you want to give administrator permissions <span class="o">(</span>optional<span class="o">)</span>: &lt;UBERNAME&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Finish.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Web: <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERNAME</span><span class="k">}</span>.<span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">UBERSERVER</span><span class="k">}</span>.uberspace.de/horde/&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Horde upgrade. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;!/usr/bin/env bash&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;pear upgrade -a -B -c horde
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>

<p><figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Horde uninstallation. </span></figcaption>
<div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
<span class='line-number'>13</span>
<span class='line-number'>14</span>
<span class='line-number'>15</span>
<span class='line-number'>16</span>
<span class='line-number'>17</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'>&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;!/usr/bin/env bash&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Uninstall horde.&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;pear uninstall &lt;code&gt;pear list -c horde <span class="p">|</span> tail -n +4 <span class="p">|</span> awk <span class="s1">&#39;{ print &quot;horde/&quot;$1 }&#39;</span>&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Sometimes it doesn<span class="p">&amp;</span>rsquo<span class="p">;</span>t work, so use:&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;pear/pear uninstall &lt;code&gt;pear/pear list -c horde <span class="p">|</span> tail -n +4 <span class="p">|</span> awk <span class="s1">&#39;{ print &quot;horde/&quot;$1 }&#39;</span>&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;Drop database. Be careful!&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;h1&gt;If you want to use it again <span class="o">(</span>e.g. reinstallation<span class="o">)</span>, DO NOT DO THIS!!!&lt;/h1&gt;
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p&gt;mysql -e <span class="p">&amp;</span>ldquo<span class="p">;</span>DROP DATABASE <span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">USER</span><span class="k">}</span>_horde<span class="p">;&amp;</span>rdquo<span class="p">;</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></p>
]]></content>
